## AUTH & ROLES\
\
### `src/lib/auth.ts`\
```typescript\
betterAuth(\{\
  database: drizzleAdapter(db, \{ provider: "pg", schema \}),\
  emailAndPassword: \{ enabled: true \},\
  plugins: [username()],\
  trustedOrigins: ["http://localhost:3000", "http://127.0.0.1:3000"],\
  user: \{ additionalFields: \{ tenantId: \{ type: "string", nullable: true, defaultValue: null \} \} \},\
\})\
```\
\
### `src/lib/auth-client.ts`\
```typescript\
createAuthClient(\{ baseURL: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_BETTER_AUTH_URL, plugins: [usernameClient()] \})\
```\
\
### `src/lib/api/auth.ts` \'97 Core Auth Helpers\
\
```typescript\
// Returns \{ userId \} \'97 no tenant. For super-admin ops only.\
async function requireAuth(): Promise<BasicAuthContext>\
\
// Looks up session \uc0\u8594  user.tenantId \u8594  getMemberByUserId(tenantId, userId) live.\
// Role changes take effect immediately (no re-login needed).\
async function requireRole(...allowedRoles: TenantRole[]): Promise<AuthContext>\
\
async function requireOperator(): Promise<AuthContext>  // operator | admin | master\
async function requireTenant():  Promise<AuthContext>   // alias for requireOperator()\
async function requireAdmin():   Promise<AuthContext>   // admin | master\
async function requireMaster():  Promise<AuthContext>   // master only\
\
// External API: reads x-tenant-id header. TODO: replace with API keys.\
function getTenantFromHeader(request: Request): string\
```\
\
**Context types:**\
```typescript\
interface BasicAuthContext \{ userId: string \}\
interface AuthContext \{ userId: string; tenantId: string; role: TenantRole; memberId: string \}\
```\
\
**Tenant resolution**: `session.user.tenantId` (set on the Better Auth `user` row). Not in the session token \'97 fetched from the `user` object on every request.\
\
**Role resolution**: `getMemberByUserId(tenantId, userId)` \'97 live DB lookup, not cached.\
