## VALIDATION ENGINE\
\
### `src/lib/validation/types.ts`\
```typescript\
interface FieldDefinitionShape \{ id, name, label, fieldType: FieldType, isRequired, validationRules: ValidationRules|null \}\
interface ValidationRule \{ rule: string; value: unknown; message?: string \}\
interface ValidationRules \{ rules: ValidationRule[] \}\
interface FieldValidationContext \{ fieldDefinition: FieldDefinitionShape; value: unknown; allValues? \}\
interface ValidationError \{ fieldId, fieldLabel, rule, message: string \}\
interface ValidationResult \{ valid: boolean; errors: ValidationError[] \}\
type ValidatorFn = (value, ruleValue, context: FieldValidationContext) => boolean\
interface RuleDefinition \{ rule, description, paramType: "number"|"string"|"boolean"|"string[]"|"iso-date", example? \}\
```\
\
### `src/lib/validation/engine.ts`\
```typescript\
validateField(context: FieldValidationContext): ValidationResult\
validateCard(fieldDefinitions: FieldDefinitionShape[], values: Record<string, unknown>): ValidationResult\
getApplicableRules(fieldType: FieldType): RuleDefinition[]\
```\
Used by `useCardForm` (frontend) and `createCard`/`updateCard` in DAL (backend).\
\
### `src/lib/validation/scan-validator.ts`\
```typescript\
// Pure TS, no DB, never throws. Unknown rules \uc0\u8594  failed check.\
function validateScan(\
  fieldValues: EnrichedFieldValue[],\
  scanValidations: ScanValidationWithField[]\
): ScanValidationResult\
\
interface ScanValidationCheck \{\
  scanValidationId, fieldDefinitionId, fieldLabel, rule: string\
  passed: boolean\
  severity: "error" | "warning"\
  message: string  // empty string when passed\
\}\
interface ScanValidationResult \{ passed: boolean; results: ScanValidationCheck[] \}\
```\
\
**`SCAN_RULE_EVALUATORS`** map (exact implementations):\
- `boolean_is_true`: `v === true`\
- `boolean_is_false`: `v === false`\
- `number_eq/gt/lt/gte/lte`: compare `v` to `(rv as \{target:number\}).target`\
- `number_between`: `v >= rv.min && v <= rv.max`\
- `date_before/after/equals`: midnight-normalized Date comparison; `\{relative:"today"\}` resolves dynamically\
\
**Scan rule JSONB value shapes**:\
```\
boolean_*       \uc0\u8594  null\
number_eq/gt/\'85  \uc0\u8594  \{ target: number \}\
number_between  \uc0\u8594  \{ min: number, max: number \}\
date_*          \uc0\u8594  \{ target: "YYYY-MM-DD" \}  OR  \{ relative: "today" \}\
```\
